<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 2:13PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central
Armstrong, southeastern Carson and west central Gray Counties through
245 PM CDT...
At 213 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northeast of Claude, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central
Armstrong, southeastern Carson and west central Gray Counties.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
